    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "BOISE, Nov. 28.-Sheriff Hodgin\nwill tomorrow begin the work OF\nsummoning 100 men for the special\nvenire ordered by Judge Wood yes\nterday in the Pettfbone trial. The\ntalesmen will report Monday for\nexamination\n\n\nClarence Darrow arrived last\nnight and on Monday will take\ncharge of the defense. Borah will\nnot take part in the trial until the\njury has been secured.\n\n\nCharles H. Meyer will be in con-\nslant attendance at the trial, but\nHaywood will not come unless sum-\nmoned as witness. A comfort\nable house has been secured for\nthe jury."
    }
  ]
